-- Saudi British Raises Bad Loan Provisions to $134.4 Million as Profit Drops
-- Mourad Haroutunian
-- 2010-07-27T11:51:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/saudi-british-raises-bad-loan-provisions-to-134-4-million-as-profit-drops.html

          
          
             Saudi British Bank , a lender 40
percent owned by HSBC Holdings Plc, almost tripled provisions
for bad loans in the second quarter.  
 Provisions rose to 504 million riyals ($134.4 million) in
the three months ended June 30, from 176.5 million riyals in the
previous quarter, according to data posted on the  Saudi bourse 
website today.  
 On July 12,  Saudi British Bank  reported a 34 percent
decline in second-quarter profit to 447 million riyals, from 676
million riyals a year earlier.  
